msgid ""
":class:`scrapy.extensions.httpcache.FilesystemCacheStorage` (default value "
"of :setting:`HTTPCACHE_STORAGE`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:662
msgid "Request fingerprints must be at least 1 byte long."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:664
msgid ""
"Path and filename length limits of the file system of :setting:"
"`HTTPCACHE_DIR` also apply. Inside :setting:`HTTPCACHE_DIR`, the following "
"directory structure is created:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:668
msgid ":attr:`.Spider.name`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:670
msgid "first byte of a request fingerprint as hexadecimal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:672
msgid "fingerprint as hexadecimal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:674
msgid "filenames up to 16 characters long"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:676
msgid ""
"For example, if a request fingerprint is made of 20 bytes (default), :"
"setting:`HTTPCACHE_DIR` is ``'/home/user/project/.scrapy/httpcache'``, and "
"the name of your spider is ``'my_spider'`` your file system must support a "
"file path like::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:681
